{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"77ad10d9-a496-4ea7-8103-e6dcccbd9f92","content":"Good news — on .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively uses Microsoft Testing Platform. You **no longer need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`**. That property was a .NET 9 bridge to opt into MTP; in .NET 10 it's the default and the property is ignored.\n\nYour `EnableMSTestRunner` is still required — it tells MSTest to build as an MTP executable.\n\nLet me clean up your project file:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_4cU81sJw02FFFBfccpf6O0","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-8b0db33bedf44507b585e4d8f83c6bcb/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-8b0db33bedf44507b585e4d8f83c6bcb/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"12b6cdb2-d779-4c29-8a0e-cb5fd6f222f1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and wants to know about Microsoft Testing Platform (MTP) support in `dotnet test`.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` has native support for Microsoft Testing Platform. The key change is:\n\n1. **`TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` is no longer needed** — .NET 10's `dotnet test` natively understands MTP. This property was a bridge for .NET 9 to opt into the MTP-based `dotnet test` experience. In .NET 10, it's the default behavior.\n\n\n2. **`EnableMSTestRunner` is still required** — this property tells MSTest to generate a self-contained test executable using MTP.\n\nSince .NET 10 uses MTP by default, the user should remove the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property but keep `EnableMSTestRunner` in their project file.","outputTokens":590,"requestId":"BD16:C42E6:1D91864:213B142:6A07C567"},"id":"dabf651e-9ebe-473e-8f91-c8b25b5a8659","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:16:34.728Z","parentId":"be96d471-4917-4